Three persons – two children and a teenager- have been confirmed killed in a fresh attack in Kauru village in Kaduna State on Monday. According to an eye witness, the attack occurred in Unguwan Rimi Village in Kauru local government area of the state around 2:30pm on Monday when unknown gunmen invaded the village and started shooting sporadically, leaving some people dead and several others injured. However, the Kaduna State Police Command, while confirming the incident, said three people were killed in the incident. In a confirmation statement issued by the Command’s Public Relations Officer, DSP Yakubu Sabo, he gave the names of the victims as; Monday Yahaya, 8, Samson David, 17 and Ashimile Danladi 9. The statement said: “Information reaching us has it that on 17/6/19 at about 14:25hrs, DPO Kauru received a distress call that armed men entered Unguwan Rimi village, Chawai District of Kauru LGA, started shooting sporadically and in the process shot dead one Monday Yahaya 8 years, Samson David 17 years and Ashimile Danladi 9 years old respectively. “Teams of Policemen quickly moved to the area, evacuated the dead bodies to the hospital and ensured that the situation was brought under control. “Preliminary investigation later revealed that the attack might not be unconnected with the attack of Fulani camp early morning of the same date in the area. “However, efforts are on to apprehend the perpetrators and the command has intensified patrols and other proactive measures to forestall further breach of peace in the area,” the statement read. Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin